# Pi-hole Configuration Template
# Copy this file to apps/pi-hole/.env and fill in secure values
#
# Generate secure passwords using:
#   openssl rand -base64 32

# Pi-hole Web Interface Password
# Used to login to the Pi-hole admin dashboard
# Access at: http://homelab-01:8080/admin
PIHOLE_ADMIN_PASSWORD=<CHANGE_ME_SECURE_PASSWORD>

# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to apps/pi-hole/.env
# 2. Set a strong admin password
# 3. Configure DNS resolution (see docs/SERVER-SETUP.md):
#    - Disable systemd-resolved
#    - Update /etc/resolv.conf to use 127.0.0.1
# 4. Start Pi-hole: cd apps/pi-hole && docker compose up -d
# 5. Access admin interface: http://homelab-01:8080/admin
# 6. Login with the password you set

# DNS Configuration Notes:
# - Pi-hole listens on port 53 (DNS)
# - Admin interface on port 8080
# - Only accessible from LAN (firewall configured)
# - Not accessible from Tailscale interface

# Security Notes:
# - Use a strong password (16+ characters)
# - Admin interface exposed to LAN only
# - Change password regularly
# - Never commit this file to version control after filling in values

# Optional: Additional Environment Variables
# Uncomment and configure as needed:
# TZ=America/New_York                    # Timezone
# WEBPASSWORD=$PIHOLE_ADMIN_PASSWORD     # Alternative variable name
# DNSMASQ_LISTENING=all                  # DNS listening mode
# DNS1=1.1.1.1                           # Upstream DNS server 1
# DNS2=8.8.8.8                           # Upstream DNS server 2
